
For monolithic : 1 EC2 instance, deploy wordpress and MYSQL on the same instances.
In this setup, both WordPress (the web application) and MySQL (the database) are installed and run on the same EC2 instance.
Step 1: Launch EC2 Instances
Navigate to EC2 Dashboard: Go to the AWS Management Console and select EC2.
Launch Instance:
Choose AMI: Search for "Ubuntu Server" and select the latest Ubuntu 20.04 LTS AMI.
Instance Type: Select t2.micro (free tier eligible).
Key Pair: Choose an existing key pair or create a new one to securely connect to the instance via SSH.


